shall a heavier penalty be imposed than the one that was applicable at the time
the penal offence was committed.<EOS> No one shall be subjected to arbitrary
interference with his privacy, family, home or correspondence, nor to attacks
upon his honour and reputation.<EOS> Everyone has the right to the protection of the
law against such interference or attacks.<EOS> (1) Everyone has the right to freedom
of movement and residence within the borders of each State.<EOS> (1) Everyone has the
